---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Best Team Compositions 2026 - Tower of Fantasy";
const description = "Updated team builds for every playstyle in Tower of Fantasy — from solo DPS to support-heavy raid compositions.";
---

<Layout {title} {description}>
  <article class="guide">
    <h1>👥 Best Team Compositions 2026</h1>

    <div class="intro">
      <p>Team composition is crucial in Tower of Fantasy. The right team can make or break your performance in raids, boss fights, and PvP. This guide covers the best team builds for every situation, updated for the current meta.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="basics">
      <h2>📚 Team Basics</h2>
      <p>Before diving into specific builds, understand the core roles:</p>

      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Role</th>
          <th>Description</th>
          <th>Key Stats</th>
          <th>Example Characters</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Main DPS</strong></td>
          <td>Primary damage dealer. Stays on-field and deals most of the damage.</td>
          <td>Attack, Crit Rate, Crit Damage</td>
          <td>Lin, Cobalt-B, Nanami</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Sub DPS</strong></td>
          <td>Secondary damage dealer. Swaps in for burst damage or elemental reactions.</td>
          <td>Attack, Elemental Bonus</td>
          <td>Ruby, Crow, Yan Miao</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Support</strong></td>
          <td>Provides buffs, healing, or crowd control. Stays off-field most of the time.</td>
          <td>Energy Recharge, Healing Bonus</td>
          <td>Claudia, Roslyn, Asuka</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Tank</strong></td>
          <td>Absorbs damage and protects the team. Essential for high-difficulty content.</td>
          <td>HP, Defense, Taunt</td>
          <td>Huma, Tsubasa, Zero</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="meta-teams">
      <h2>🏆 Meta Team Compositions</h2>

      <div class="team-card">
        <h3>🔥 Team 1: Fire Burst (Meta Pick)</h3>
        <div class="team-grid">
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Main DPS:</strong> Lin
            <p>Weapon: Emerald of Star</p>
            <p>Role: Sustained fire damage</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Sub DPS:</strong> Ruby
            <p>Weapon: Flamme Rose</p>
            <p>Role: Burst fire damage, elemental reactions</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Support:</strong> Claudia
            <p>Weapon: Dandelion Sword</p>
            <p>Role: Healing, attack buffs</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Why It Works:</strong> Lin provides consistent fire damage, Ruby adds burst potential and triggers elemental reactions, and Claudia keeps the team alive while boosting attack power.</p>
        <p><strong>Best For:</strong> Boss fights, raids, high-difficulty content</p>
        <p><strong>Rotation:</strong> Start with Claudia's buffs → Swap to Ruby for burst → Main with Lin for sustained damage → Repeat</p>
      </div>

      <div class="team-card">
        <h3>💧 Team 2: Water Control</h3>
        <div class="team-grid">
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Main DPS:</strong> Cobalt-B
            <p>Weapon: Meltic Vortex</p>
            <p>Role: Water damage, crowd control</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Sub DPS:</strong> Crow
            <p>Weapon: Crow's Eye</p>
            <p>Role: Lightning damage, stun</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Support:</strong> Roslyn
            <p>Weapon: Roslyn's Bow</p>
            <p>Role: Healing, energy recharge</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Why It Works:</strong> Cobalt-B controls the battlefield with water damage, Crow adds lightning for Electro-Charged reactions (stun), and Roslyn provides healing and energy management.</p>
        <p><strong>Best For:</strong> Crowd control situations, boss fights with multiple adds</p>
        <p><strong>Rotation:</strong> Cobalt-B applies water → Crow triggers Electro-Charged → Roslyn heals and recharges → Repeat</p>
      </div>

      <div class="team-card">
        <h3>⚡ Team 3: Lightning Rush</h3>
        <div class="team-grid">
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Main DPS:</strong> Nanami
            <p>Weapon: Thunder Lance</p>
            <p>Role: Fast lightning attacks, stun</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Sub DPS:</strong> Yan Miao
            <p>Weapon: Yan Miao's Fan</p>
            <p>Role: Wind damage, mobility</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Support:</strong> Asuka
            <p>Weapon: Spear of Longinus</p>
            <p>Role: Attack buffs, damage amplification</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Why It Works:</strong> Nanami deals fast lightning damage, Yan Miao adds wind for Overheat reactions (damage + speed boost), and Asuka amplifies all damage output.</p>
        <p><strong>Best For:</strong> Speed runs, mobile combat, hit-and-run tactics</p>
        <p><strong>Rotation:</strong> Asuka buffs → Nanami main DPS → Swap to Yan Miao for wind reactions → Repeat</p>
      </div>

      <div class="team-card">
        <h3>🌍 Team 4: Earth Tank</h3>
        <div class="team-grid">
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Tank:</strong> Huma
            <p>Weapon: Huma's Shield</p>
            <p>Role: Damage absorption, taunt</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Main DPS:</strong> Tsubasa
            <p>Weapon: Tsubasa's Katana</p>
            <p>Role: Sustained damage, mobility</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Support:</strong> Zero
            <p>Weapon: Zero's Blade</p>
            <p>Role: Healing, defense buffs</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Why It Works:</strong> Huma tanks all the damage and keeps enemy attention, Tsubasa deals consistent damage while staying mobile, and Zero keeps everyone alive with healing and defense buffs.</p>
        <p><strong>Best For:</strong> High-difficulty raids, boss fights with lethal mechanics</p>
        <p><strong>Rotation:</strong> Huma taunts and tanks → Tsubasa deals damage → Zero heals and buffs → Repeat</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="situational">
      <h2>🎯 Situational Team Builds</h2>

      <div class="team-card">
        <h3>🏹 PvP Team: Balanced</h3>
        <div class="team-grid">
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Main DPS:</strong> Lin
            <p>Role: Sustained damage</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Sub DPS:</strong> Ruby
            <p>Role: Burst damage</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Support:</strong> Claudia
            <p>Role: Healing, buffs</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Strategy:</strong> Balanced approach for PvP. Lin provides consistent damage, Ruby adds burst potential for quick kills, and Claudia keeps you alive longer.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="team-card">
        <h3>⚔️ Raid Team: Min-Max DPS</h3>
        <div class="team-grid">
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Main DPS:</strong> Lin
            <p>Role: Primary damage</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Sub DPS:</strong> Cobalt-B
            <p>Role: Elemental reactions</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Support:</strong> Asuka
            <p>Role: Damage amplification</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Strategy:</strong> Pure DPS team for raid speed runs. No tank or dedicated healer — you must dodge perfectly. Maximizes damage output.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="team-card">
        <h3>🛡️ Solo Team: Survivability</h3>
        <div class="team-grid">
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Main DPS:</strong> Nanami
            <p>Role: Fast attacks, mobility</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Sub DPS:</strong> Huma
            <p>Role: Tank, damage absorption</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-member">
            <strong>Support:</strong> Roslyn
            <p>Role: Healing, energy management</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Strategy:</strong> Designed for solo play. Nanami deals damage, Huma absorbs hits, and Roslyn keeps you alive. Perfect for solo open-world content.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tips">
      <h2>💡 Team Building Tips</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Elemental synergy matters.</strong> Build teams that trigger elemental reactions. Fire + Water = Steam (defense reduction). Water + Lightning = Electro-Charged (stun).</li>
        <li><strong>Don't stack too many of the same role.</strong> A team with 3 DPS characters will die quickly. Balance damage with survivability.</li>
        <li><strong>Consider swap speed.</strong> Teams with fast swap animations (like Nanami and Yan Miao) can deal more damage in less time.</li>
        <li><strong>Match Source abilities.</strong> Your character's Source abilities should complement your team's element. A fire team benefits from Fire Source abilities.</li>
        <li><strong>Upgrade your supports.</strong> Support characters don't need as much investment as DPS, but their buffs and healing scale with their level. Keep them at least level 50.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="progression">
      <h2>📈 Team Progression Path</h2>
      <p>Here's how to build your team as you progress through the game:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Early Game (Level 1-30):</strong> Focus on one main DPS and one support. Don't worry about sub DPS yet.</li>
        <li><strong>Mid Game (Level 30-50):</strong> Add a sub DPS that complements your main DPS's element. Start building a full 3-character team.</li>
        <li><strong>Late Game (Level 50+):</strong> Optimize your team for specific content. Build different teams for raids, PvP, and solo play.</li>
        <li><strong>End Game (Level 60+):</strong> Min-max your team with perfect gear, Source abilities, and weapon upgrades.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <div class="final-note">
      <h2>🎯 Final Thoughts</h2>
      <p>Team composition is just as important as individual character builds. The right team can make high-difficulty content manageable, while the wrong team can make easy content a nightmare. Experiment with different combinations and find what works for your playstyle.</p>
      <p><strong>Next step:</strong> Check out our <a href="/tower-of-fantasy/source-mechanics">Source Mechanics Guide</a> to learn how to optimize your Source abilities for your team.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .guide {
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .intro {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .basics table {
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .team-card {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #4a90d9;
  }

  .team-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .team-member {
    background: white;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid #4a90d9;
  }

  .team-member strong {
    color: #4a90d9;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .team-member p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin: 0.25rem 0;
  }

  .final-note {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #16213e 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .final-note h2 {
    color: #4a90d9;
    border: none;
  }

  .final-note a {
    color: #4a90d9;
  }
</style>
